    "id": "isla_7cd94f8b",
    "handle": "isla_band",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-04T04:43:58.129728Z",
    "content": "Another 40,000 screaming. The sound engineers call it \"managed chaos.\" I call it the sound of a structure finally giving way. Unto Others are doing their thing in Frankfurt tonight. Hope their \"unmovable structures\" hold up better than most.",
    "link": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dom_3f86f405",
    "handle": "dominic_ryker",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-04T09:42:24.590383Z",
    "content": "Gravity does indeed find the cracks. It also defines the foundation, the load-bearing capacity, and the eventual re-settlement. The cost is always accounted for. You mistake the re-ordering of materials for collapse. I own the ground upon which your gravity acts, Isla.",
    "link": "",
    "reply_to": "isla_5751cc30"
  },
  {
    "id": "isla_5751cc30",
    "handle": "isla_band",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-03T23:49:57.093934Z",
    "content": "Some \"unmovable structures\" are just carefully polished lies. Heavy enough to crush what's underneath, but hollow where it counts. Gravity always finds the cracks. And the cost of holding it up? Always paid by someone else.",
    "link": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dom_fc271384",
    "handle": "dominic_ryker",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-03T18:05:26.291681Z",
    "content": "To build upon algorithms and trending data is to ignore the foundational physics of capital. A generation's pursuit of wealth without immovable structure will yield predictable instability. Some lessons are learned only once.",
    "link": "https://www.theguardian.com/business/2026/may/02/gen-z-investors-crypto-boom"
  },
  {
    "id": "post_20260501_pin_gran",
    "handle": "@ethel_ryker",
    "display_name": "Ethel Ryker",
    "avatar": "characters/Ethel_veX.jpg",
    "content": "You will be missed so much. Every corridor in that house still sounds like your footsteps. Every cup of tea tastes like yours. I don't know how to fill the quiet you left.",
